 Compliance and Exceptions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Compliance with this policy is mandatory for all County personnel engaged in technology procurement or technology-related financial activity.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Assessment
\series default
:
 Compliance shall be assessed through procurement review activities,
 audit support activities,
 and the annual policy review process defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Annual Policy Review and Maturity Scoring).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Enforcement
\series default
:
 Non-compliance may result in corrective actions defined under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Policy Implementation,
 Enforcement,
 and Legal Alignment).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Emergency Deviations
\series default
:
 When immediate technology procurement is necessary to protect life,
 safety,
 or critical infrastructure and delay would materially increase harm,
 the IT Director or the Assistant IT Director may authorize Emergency Technical Approval.
 A technical approver formally delegated under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 may issue Emergency Technical Approval only within the scope of that written delegation.
 Emergency Technical Approval does not constitute purchasing authority,
 contract execution authority,
 or payment authorization;
 these remain subject to the Office of Fiscal Affairs and applicable emergency-contract requirements under NRS 332.112.
 Emergency Technical Approval shall satisfy the following constraints:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The invoking authority shall document a written emergency basis establishing the threat to life,
 safety,
 or critical infrastructure and the time constraints that preclude the standard Technical Approval process.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The invoking authority shall notify the Office of Fiscal Affairs within twenty-four (24) hours of authorization.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
When Emergency Technical Approval is issued by a technical approver delegated under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 the delegated approver shall notify the IT Director within twenty-four (24) hours of authorization.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The invoking authority shall submit complete post-incident documentation —
 including the written emergency basis,
 the Emergency Technical Approval record,
 inventory capture,
 and asset or CMDB entry —
 within ten (10) business days of the emergency action.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Emergency Technical Approval authority does not extend beyond the specific transaction required to address the immediate harm;
 subsequent related procurements shall follow the standard Technical-Fiscal Handshake.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The IT Director shall review all Emergency Technical Approval authorizations on a quarterly basis.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The IT Director shall report the inventory of emergency invocations,
 their written bases,
 and their post-incident documentation status as part of the annual policy review under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exceptions
\series default
:
 Standing exceptions to this policy shall be documented with justification and approved in writing in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
