\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Elko County shall separate 
\series bold
Technical Authority
\series default
 (validation of technology need,
 compatibility,
 lifecycle and architectural impact,
 inventory integration,
 and security) from 
\series bold
Financial Authority
\series default
 (budget verification and lawful purchasing execution).
 This separation exists to prevent unauthorized technology acquisition,
 ensure value realization,
 and maintain auditability of public funds consistent with Nevada Revised Statutes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 The Technical-Fiscal Handshake
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
All technology spending shall pass through a mandatory two-step validation:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Technical Approval
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall record Technical Approval as a distinct approval status on the procurement work order in the System of Engagement,
 including approver identity and timestamp.
 Email correspondence and verbal assent shall not constitute Technical Approval.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Financial Approval
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Office of Fiscal Affairs shall validate budget availability prior to authorizing payment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Office of Fiscal Affairs shall verify that purchasing actions comply with applicable procurement requirements,
 including competitive bidding thresholds and required documentation under NRS 332.
\end_layout

\end_deeper

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Handshake Restrictions
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Office of Fiscal Affairs shall not treat a budget line item as authorization to procure;
 Technical Approval is required.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Office of Fiscal Affairs shall not process payment without documented Technical Approval.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Information Operations Department shall not integrate,
 support,
 or onboard technology resources acquired without documented Technical Approval.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2 Procurement Controls and Shadow IT Prohibition
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Centralized Procurement
\series default
:
 All County personnel shall route County software,
 hardware,
 and cloud subscription procurement through the Information Operations Department to ensure security review,
 asset tagging,
 license compliance,
 and CMDB and inventory integration.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
P-Card Restrictions
\series default
:
 County personnel shall not use departmental P-Cards for technology hardware,
 software,
 or subscriptions without written pre-authorization by the IT Director or a formally delegated technical approver.
 The Office of Fiscal Affairs shall flag suspected technology P-Card transactions for review and audit.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Grant-Funded Technology
\series default
:
 Grant-funded technology shall be subject to the same standards as County-funded assets,
 including security requirements,
 inventory and CMDB entry,
 supportability,
 and lifecycle cost planning.
 Department Heads shall engage the Information Operations Department during grant application development to validate technical feasibility and total cost of ownership.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Auto-Renewal Controls
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall disable auto-renewal on technology subscriptions when vendor contract terms permit.
 When auto-renewal cannot be disabled due to vendor contract terms,
 the Assistant IT Director shall initiate renewal review not less than sixty (60) calendar days before each renewal date to prevent unmanaged commitments.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Bid Splitting
\series default
:
 County personnel shall not split a single technology procurement requirement into multiple smaller transactions to evade competitive bidding thresholds established by NRS 332.063 and NRS 332.065.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 Budgeting and Security Resource Allocation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Security Resourcing
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall plan,
 request,
 and maintain discrete funding necessary to implement required security controls and compliance obligations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Lifecycle Forecasting
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall include Total Cost of Ownership (TCO) considerations in technology budget submissions,
 including licensing,
 maintenance,
 support,
 required security controls,
 power and cooling (as applicable),
 and end-of-life disposal.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.4 Asset Intake Handshake
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Office of Fiscal Affairs shall not approve payment for technology hardware,
 software,
 or Software-as-a-Service invoices without the asset intake confirmations required under 
