\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.5 Vendor Integrity and Contract Security Requirements
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Conflict of Interest and Gifts
\series default
:
 All County personnel participating in technology procurement decisions shall comply with the Zero-Gift Policy and Vendor Interaction requirements established under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Code of Ethics and Professional Conduct).
 Personnel shall disclose any actual or potential conflict of interest in writing to the IT Director prior to participating in a procurement decision.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Contract Security Requirements
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall ensure that contracts involving County data exchange,
 hosting,
 or access to County systems incorporate the security and data protection terms established under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.06"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Vendor Compliance and Third-Party Assurance Policy).
 Department Heads shall not execute technology contracts that omit these required terms.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
CJIS Contractor Requirements
\series default
:
 When a vendor or contractor may have logical or physical access to Criminal Justice Information (CJI):
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The IT Director (as LASO) shall require incorporation of the CJIS Security Addendum into the contract consistent with CJIS Security Policy v6.0 SA-9 (External System Services) and Appendix H.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The IT Director (as LASO) shall ensure that each contractor employee with CJI access is provided a copy of the CJIS Security Addendum and the CJIS Security Policy,
 and that an executed Security Addendum Certification is obtained acknowledging receipt and agreement to comply.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall retain executed certifications and acknowledgments in the department's records retention system.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall ensure that executed certifications and acknowledgments remain available for audit.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.6 Records Retention
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall retain Information Operations procurement artifacts and tracking records —
 including Technical Approval records,
 procurement work order linkages,
 receiving confirmations,
 and inventory and CMDB reconciliation data —
 in accordance with LRDA 20070074 (Requisitions and Purchase Orders),
 LRDA 20071310 (Procurement and Credit Card Records),
 NRS 239.125 (Local Government Records Management Program),
 and NAC 239.155 (Adoption of Records Retention Schedule).
 Official purchasing and payment records —
 including purchase orders,
 invoices,
 and payment vouchers —
 shall be retained by the Office of Fiscal Affairs or the authoritative County custodian under the applicable retention schedule.
\end_layout

